05:23.197 --> 05:25.158
Please,
just stop trying to be Daddy.

05:25.241 --> 05:27.243
Seriously.
It's deeply upsetting.

05:27.326 --> 05:28.369
- Fine.

05:28.453 --> 05:30.413
You're so bothered by this,
okay, I'll swap seats,

05:30.496 --> 05:32.040
if it'll make you
fucking happy.

05:32.123 --> 05:34.584
Move the fuck down. Come on.

05:34.667 --> 05:36.252
Judy's got
a wild hair up her ass

05:36.335 --> 05:38.504
about people sitting
where they're gonna sit.

05:38.588 --> 05:40.298
Here we go.
Let's all sit on the side

05:40.381 --> 05:41.674
like a bunch of idiots.

05:41.758 --> 05:43.468
Absolutely ridiculous.

05:43.551 --> 05:45.261
You happy?
- I am happy.

05:45.344 --> 05:46.929
- Empty chair
at the head of the table.

05:47.013 --> 05:48.014
- Eli wouldn't want this.

05:48.097 --> 05:50.099
- You know what else
he wouldn't want?

05:50.183 --> 05:53.603
He wouldn't want you
making up stupid-ass hashtags,

05:53.686 --> 05:55.563
peacocking all over his stage

05:55.646 --> 05:57.398
like you're Hota Kotb
or some shit.

05:57.482 --> 05:59.192
- Jesse and I made
a heartfelt statement.

05:59.275 --> 06:00.568
- That statement should have
been made

06:00.651 --> 06:01.736
by the primary Gemstones.

06:01.819 --> 06:02.820
That's who should've said it.

06:02.904 --> 06:04.322
- Okay.
- [grumbling]

06:08.951 --> 06:10.078
- Oh, God.

06:12.997 --> 06:15.124
[chair scrapes]

06:21.506 --> 06:22.840
Where the fuck have you been?

06:22.924 --> 06:24.592
- And what the fuck
are you wearing?

06:24.675 --> 06:25.802
- I'm not prepared

06:25.885 --> 06:27.387
to present myself
in public yet.

06:27.470 --> 06:29.972
I only broke my solitude
to inquire how Daddy is.

06:30.056 --> 06:31.641
- This is the motherfucker
that hasn't even visited

06:31.724 --> 06:33.101
Daddy in the hospital yet.

06:33.184 --> 06:34.936
- I'm recovering, Jesse.

06:35.019 --> 06:36.896
I can't do anything
with these hands.

06:36.979 --> 06:38.773
I look like a--a beast.

06:38.856 --> 06:40.316
- Yeah, you look like
damn "Beaty and the Beast"

06:40.399 --> 06:42.110
wearing that fucking cloak.
- And guess what?

06:42.193 --> 06:43.820
Your thumbs look like
the fucking Elephant Man.

06:43.903 --> 06:46.572
- Do not mock my thumbs--
[shouting]

06:46.656 --> 06:48.491
Oh! Oh!

06:48.574 --> 06:50.159
- You know, y'all are shameful.

06:50.243 --> 06:52.537
Sometimes I feel like I'm
the only person in this family

06:52.620 --> 06:53.788
that knows how to fill
a power void.

06:53.871 --> 06:55.289
- That's it.
- What's it?

06:55.373 --> 06:57.166
- I'm gonna flick
this fucking cream corn

06:57.250 --> 06:58.292
on your fucking face.

06:58.376 --> 07:00.169
- Enough!
Good Lord.

07:00.253 --> 07:03.339
Your father is hurt,
and this is how you act?

07:03.422 --> 07:06.092
All you ever do is--is fight
about what you can get.

07:06.175 --> 07:08.845
Can't you just be kind
to each other?

07:08.928 --> 07:11.222
Self-absorbed, loud,

07:11.305 --> 07:14.016
arrogant fucking assholes!

07:20.231 --> 07:21.315
- Shit, y'all.

07:21.399 --> 07:23.317
- Martin's right.

07:23.401 --> 07:25.111
Y'all a bunch of a-holes.

07:25.194 --> 07:27.113
- He was talking to you too,
dick-lips.

07:29.657 --> 07:31.367
- Fresh rolls from Jason's,
Daddy.

07:31.450 --> 07:32.368
I know you can't eat 'em,

07:32.451 --> 07:35.329
but I thought you might like
to smell 'em.

07:36.914 --> 07:39.333
Don't it make you just wanna
open your eyes and talk?

07:39.417 --> 07:43.504
[machines beeping]

07:43.588 --> 07:46.883
Just please don't die, okay?

07:46.966 --> 07:49.093
Please, Daddy, I promise
if you pull through this,

07:49.177 --> 07:51.095
I'll be a more
loving and caring

07:51.179 --> 07:54.265
person, sister, and friend.

07:54.348 --> 07:56.726
[tender music]

07:56.809 --> 07:59.145
Just come back to us, okay?

08:01.647 --> 08:02.857
- I've been praying
for guidance

08:02.940 --> 08:04.358
on how to navigate this.

08:04.442 --> 08:06.194
I heard about
this great opportunity.

08:06.277 --> 08:08.696
It's a movie,
and they need stunt performers.

08:08.779 --> 08:09.864
- You're going
back to California?

08:09.947 --> 08:11.532
- No, that's the thing.
It's not even that far away.

08:11.616 --> 08:13.201
It's filming right next door
in Atlanta.

08:13.284 --> 08:14.368
- No.

08:14.452 --> 08:15.494
Absolutely not.

08:15.578 --> 08:17.163
Your grandfather is
in the hospital,

08:17.246 --> 08:19.040
and you're talking about
going to Atlanta

08:19.123 --> 08:20.625
to do stunt stuff?

08:20.708 --> 08:22.210
- I realize that this is
the worst timing ever.

08:22.293 --> 08:23.711
You know, I really do.

08:23.794 --> 08:26.255
And you know the last thing
I wanna do is let you down.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.966
That being said,

08:29.050 --> 08:30.927
I feel myself
settling into a life here

08:31.010 --> 08:34.096
that doesn't seem authentic
to me.

08:34.180 --> 08:36.390
The things that are important
to this family,

08:36.474 --> 08:39.018
I'm just not so sure
they are to me.

08:39.101 --> 08:41.604
So...
- So what?

08:41.687 --> 08:43.231
- I'm moving out.

08:43.314 --> 08:46.234
[solemn music]

08:46.317 --> 08:49.862
♪ ♪

08:49.946 --> 08:52.156
- You gonna say something,
Jesse?

08:52.240 --> 08:54.575
- Yeah.
Yeah, what the fuck, Gideon?

08:54.659 --> 08:56.953
You're talking more
about his Hollywood bullshit?

08:57.036 --> 08:59.413
- I thought you and I made some
real progress in Haiti, Dad.

08:59.497 --> 09:01.916
I thought we finally started
understanding each other.

09:01.999 --> 09:03.543
- You have been wrong,
it seems,

09:03.626 --> 09:04.669
about a lot of things.

09:04.752 --> 09:06.420
Isn't that right, Jesse?

09:08.214 --> 09:09.340
Jesse.
- Yes.

09:09.423 --> 09:10.508
Yes, your mother is right.

09:10.591 --> 09:13.302
We all know what happens
when you chase your dreams.

09:13.386 --> 09:15.805
You fail and people end up
getting robbed

09:15.888 --> 09:18.099
and--and almost killed.

09:19.684 --> 09:22.019
Sometimes killed,
for--for some people.

09:22.103 --> 09:23.104
- Mm-hmm.

09:24.939 --> 09:27.441
- Looks like a bunch
of charges in Winston-Salem.

09:27.525 --> 09:29.402
A charge today at a Bojangles.

09:29.485 --> 09:33.656
- And then it says
he went to the Fo--Fo--

09:34.991 --> 09:38.619
Fossil Watch Store.

09:38.703 --> 09:42.790
At the T--T--

09:42.873 --> 09:47.378
- Sound it out. Tanger--
- Tanger Outlets.

09:47.461 --> 09:48.629
- Got it.

09:48.713 --> 09:49.797
Very good, Tiffany.

09:49.880 --> 09:51.591
Your reading's getting
much better.

09:51.674 --> 09:53.509
- So either Baby Billy's
outlet shopping,

09:53.592 --> 09:56.846
or it's the people
who murdered and robbed him.

09:56.929 --> 09:59.807
- Yes, that's probably
what we're looking at.

09:59.890 --> 10:01.350
One of those things.

10:01.434 --> 10:02.768
- Take me there.

10:04.145 --> 10:07.023
- Okay, so obviously,
this fellow we're dealing with

10:07.106 --> 10:08.983
is a certified psychopath.

10:09.066 --> 10:10.985
